1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,388
Kick the murderer out!

2
00:00:14,389 --> 00:00:15,889
Kick him out!

3
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:18,475
What did our kids do to deserve this?

4
00:00:18,476 --> 00:00:20,269
What did our kids do?

5
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,271
Isolate the murderer!

6
00:00:22,272 --> 00:00:24,732
Isolate him!

7
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,108
It's Cho Gyu-cheol!

8
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,861
- Bastard! How dare you come here!
- Cho Gyu-cheol!

9
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:30,487
- Look over here!
- You're not human!

10
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:31,656
Drop out, you bastard!

11
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:34,658
- How dare you go in!
- This is outrageous!

12
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:36,535
Kick him out, for God's sake!

13
00:00:36,536 --> 00:00:40,707
You expect our kids to go to school
with him? Kick him out!

14
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:44,585
<i>Cho Gyu-cheol has shown
deep remorse for his crimes,</i>

15
00:00:44,586 --> 00:00:49,174
<i>followed the correctional facility rules,
and set an example for others.</i>

16
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:52,176
<i>Given his minor status and clean record,</i>

17
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:57,182
<i>the committee finds no risk of recidivism
and hereby grants parole.</i>

18
00:01:24,209 --> 00:01:25,668
What do you think, sir?

19
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:28,505
I'm talking about Cho Gyu-cheol.

20
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:36,512
He was paroled
as soon as he completed his minimum term.

21
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:38,889
When the Educational Rights Committee
signed off,

22
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:41,892
they approved his readmission
almost instantly.

23
00:01:41,893 --> 00:01:44,853
Everything lining up perfectly,
as if planned, feels off.

24
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:47,690
It's worth looking into, isn't it?

25
00:01:48,191 --> 00:01:50,318
Readmission
is at the principal's discretion.

26
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:53,237
Cho Gyu-cheol has already been punished,

27
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:57,784
and the ERPB has no authority to deny
a student the chance to return to school.

28
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:01,746
If I stopped him...

29
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:06,501
that would be revenge.

30
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:11,505
Where's Inspector Na?

31
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:14,175
He had to stop by somewhere
before coming in.

32
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:17,887
Where?

33
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:07,645
TEACH YOU A LESSON

34
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:10,440
You look good in your uniform, don't you?

35
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,109
Don't be nervous.

36
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:16,362
I'm here as an ERPB inspector today.

37
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:18,823
You're a test case

38
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:21,909
to see if kids like you
can handle school again,

39
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:23,952
if rehabilitation is possible,

40
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,496
and if you deserve

41
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:28,875
another chance.

42
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:32,253
I will

43
00:03:33,296 --> 00:03:34,463
really do my best.

44
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:37,007
No, just don't do anything.

45
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,135
Just breathe and live quietly.

46
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:40,762
Live a normal life.

47
00:03:42,931 --> 00:03:44,432
Live like a student.

48
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:52,774
I'm sure you know what I mean.

49
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,838
This is Cho Gyu-cheol,
back in school today.

50
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:19,384
He's older than you, so be nice.

51
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:22,262
- Say hi.
- Okay.

52
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:26,474
I'll make sure
I don't get in the way of your studies.

53
00:04:28,142 --> 00:04:29,394
Nice to meet you.

54
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:37,943
What?

55
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:40,071
- Jong-su.
- What, dumbass?

56
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:42,865
How could you... to a teacher...

57
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:46,660
Seong-gu, call 119, for fuck's sake!

58
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,329
Hey, stab him again.

59
00:04:48,871 --> 00:04:50,247
Damn, you're no fun.

60
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,708
Hey.

61
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,584
I heard you killed someone.

62
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:56,087
A teacher, no less.

63
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:00,925
Wow, fucking hell.
Check out the look in his eyes.

64
00:05:02,218 --> 00:05:03,428
You gonna kill me too?

65
00:05:09,225 --> 00:05:11,602
A goddamn murderer, studying?

66
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:19,068
You feel this is unfair?
You want me to speak politely to you?

67
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,363
No, it's fine. Speak however you want.

68
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,365
Damn, you're chill.

69
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:26,366
Behave yourself.

70
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:30,121
If you act up and the ERPB shows up,
you'll be in trouble too.

71
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:32,040
Get it?

72
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,960
Yeah, I will. Thanks for the advice.

73
00:05:36,544 --> 00:05:38,171
What the hell? Let's go.

74
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:41,341
Cigs.

75
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:43,550
- What a loser.
- Hey, are you coming?

76
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,761
Yeah, coming.

77
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:14,290
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

78
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,932
It's hilarious seeing him act all shy.

79
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,558
Hey, show me the picture.

80
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,644
Shit, I got a text.

81
00:06:35,144 --> 00:06:35,978
Here, look.

82
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:42,777
That looks good too.

83
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:44,779
- Holy shit, hold on.
- Why?

84
00:06:45,446 --> 00:06:46,406
I got an S-class.

85
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:48,573
Screw you.

86
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:50,575
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

87
00:06:50,576 --> 00:06:52,536
Oh man, this is insane.

88
00:06:52,537 --> 00:06:53,703
What's the matter?

89
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:56,039
It's a report about a student
assaulting a teacher

90
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,333
after being told not to use their phone.

91
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:00,710
He challenged the teacher
under Yatcha rules.

92
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:02,505
Yatcha rules? What's that?

93
00:07:03,339 --> 00:07:06,508
It's a bare-knuckle fight.
No rank, no rules.

94
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,385
We're doing everything we can,

95
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:10,471
yet things like this keep happening.

96
00:07:12,849 --> 00:07:14,517
What are you doing out there? Come in.

97
00:07:15,017 --> 00:07:17,060
Someone is here to see you.

98
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:18,020
Bring them in.

99
00:07:18,938 --> 00:07:19,772
Okay.

100
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:48,801
Right.

101
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,680
What brings you here?

102
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:55,141
I have something to tell you.

103
00:07:56,058 --> 00:07:57,977
You've got some nerve coming here!

104
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,645
This is the ERPB.

105
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:03,691
Any student can come here.

106
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:05,276
Have a seat.

107
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,496
So what brings you here?

108
00:08:17,455 --> 00:08:19,499
I'm here to report bullying at school.

109
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:24,045
Ms. Choi once told me

110
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,713
that looking out
for others who are struggling

111
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:28,757
is something students should also learn.

112
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,884
How dare you say her name!

113
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,093
Inspector Im Han-rim.

114
00:08:32,094 --> 00:08:34,055
Aren't any of you angry?

115
00:08:34,555 --> 00:08:35,972
Inspector Im Han-rim.

116
00:08:35,973 --> 00:08:38,059
Go outside and get some air.

117
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:39,393
Okay?

118
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,188
Come on, let's go.

119
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:46,526
All right.

120
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:52,865
Finish what you were saying.

121
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:56,953
I'm sorry for bringing up Ms. Choi's name.

122
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:08,506
This is the kid getting bullied.

123
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:16,681
<i>He's definitely up to something.</i>

124
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:20,851
But the information he gave us
was pretty specific.

125
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:22,477
He's right.

126
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:25,523
Cho Gyu-cheol isn't an exception.
We'll do as we always have.

127
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,776
Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae,
this case is yours.

128
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,696
- Yes, sir.
- No, I'll go.

129
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,573
You can't, sir. Instead, I will--

130
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:36,993
Is there a reason why I can't go?

131
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:40,496
Stop him, won't you?

132
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:42,415
Should I stop you?

133
00:09:43,457 --> 00:09:45,126
Stop the traffic instead.

134
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:48,087
- Oh dear.
- I'm sorry.

135
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:53,509
Don't even think about
telling any jokes, anywhere.

136
00:09:55,052 --> 00:09:56,011
Get going.

137
00:09:56,012 --> 00:09:56,928
Okay.

138
00:09:56,929 --> 00:10:00,391
- You shouldn't laugh at his jokes.
- I'll see you later.

139
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:01,809
Deputy Bong.

140
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:03,603
Oh, come on. Not now.

141
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,897
Don't try to stop me. I'm not traffic.

142
00:10:07,857 --> 00:10:09,274
I laughed. I'm so annoyed.

143
00:10:09,275 --> 00:10:10,609
What's wrong with...

144
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,319
- I'm sorry, Minister.
- Don't laugh.

145
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,696
You shouldn't laugh.

146
00:10:14,196 --> 00:10:15,197
Oh man, I laughed.

147
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,707
JINWON HIGH SCHOOL

148
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,209
<i>Jang Seong-gu from my class?</i>

149
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,254
Seong-gu is being bullied?

150
00:10:33,007 --> 00:10:35,635
He didn't seem to have any problems
from the outside.

151
00:10:36,218 --> 00:10:37,510
<i>He has a lot of friends,</i>

152
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:42,016
<i>and Seong-gu himself said
he was enjoying school.</i>

153
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:44,434
We'll sing "Emergency Room" at karaoke.

154
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:46,187
- No.
- What?

155
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:49,314
Stop stuffing your face with my chips.

156
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,441
Okay.

157
00:10:52,568 --> 00:10:53,653
That's lit.

158
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,572
- What the...
- Hey, what's going on?

159
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,449
Why is it lagging?

160
00:11:01,118 --> 00:11:02,411
Where did Jang Seong-gu go?

161
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:09,502
Why are you nervous? Did I scare you?

162
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:11,003
Well...

163
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,046
You're from the ERPB.

164
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:14,298
Yeah.

165
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:15,965
Do you know why I'm here?

166
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:17,801
No, I don't.

167
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:20,346
We were tipped off
that someone was being bullied.

168
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:22,890
That doesn't happen here.

169
00:11:23,974 --> 00:11:24,850
Excuse me.

170
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:28,145
Let's see.

171
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:31,773
- Say, "Ah."
- What?

172
00:11:31,774 --> 00:11:32,942
Come on, say, "Ah."

173
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,321
At least you weren't hit.

174
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:40,700
Oh man, it's not me.

175
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:42,743
I'll be on my way.

176
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:44,704
Are you Wi-Fi?

177
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:51,419
Do you turn your hotspot on so the kids
can use their phones and play games?

178
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:53,629
Are you a human Wi-Fi?

179
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,634
You're always at the center,
like people gathering around Wi-Fi.

180
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:02,762
<i>And you're always the first one
to take out your phone.</i>

181
00:12:02,763 --> 00:12:04,681
<i>You probably do that</i>

182
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,893
<i>to turn your hotspot on
so they can connect to Wi-Fi.</i>

183
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:12,732
Also, you're the only one
carrying around that huge power bank.

184
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:15,317
You can't let the Wi-Fi go down, can you?

185
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:23,909
I'm really not a human Wi-Fi.

186
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,703
But seriously, I really have to go.

187
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:28,622
I'll be going now. Yeah.

188
00:12:30,082 --> 00:12:31,374
Hey, the punk's here.

189
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,918
Hey, Jang Seong-gu.
What are you doing here?

190
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:35,253
Well, a moment ago...

191
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:37,839
I was just walking, and the ERPB...

192
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,383
Holy fuck. It's the ERPB.

193
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:42,010
Watch your language.

194
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:44,180
What's the ERPB doing at our school?

195
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:46,306
Fuck, I know.

196
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:47,599
Is it Cho Gyu-cheol?

197
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,267
No, I'm here because of you.

198
00:12:49,268 --> 00:12:50,853
I heard you're a bully.

199
00:12:51,479 --> 00:12:53,355
- Me?
- Yeah.

200
00:12:55,107 --> 00:12:56,649
Who did I bully?

201
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:59,611
I told you no!

202
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:03,114
Please don't accuse innocent people.
It's really not like that!

203
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:05,992
Why are you upsetting our sweet Seong-gu?

204
00:13:05,993 --> 00:13:08,036
Seong-gu, that's enough, man.

205
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:10,080
The ERPB can make mistakes too.

206
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:12,958
Can we go now?

207
00:13:13,667 --> 00:13:14,667
Sure.

208
00:13:14,668 --> 00:13:16,879
- Okay. Goodbye, sir.
- Yeah.

209
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,339
Let's go.

210
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:22,342
Hey, you scared me there.
I thought you'd vanished.

211
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:23,886
Were you here all along?

212
00:13:24,386 --> 00:13:26,096
Why are you all sweaty, Seong-gu?

213
00:13:28,891 --> 00:13:30,308
Hey, squad up.

214
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:31,560
I got a legendary item.

215
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:34,437
Don't engage now.

216
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:35,439
- Stay back.
- Okay.

217
00:13:36,565 --> 00:13:37,566
Bong Geun-dae?

218
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,569
Hey, you're Geun-dae, right?
Bong Geun-dae.

219
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:44,531
- Yeah. Yes.
- It's been ages. How are you?

220
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:47,158
Yeah, I'm good. What about you?

221
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:50,788
I heard you're a civil servant.
I think I heard where you worked.

222
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:52,247
The ERPB? Right?

223
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,456
- The ERPB.
- Wait.

224
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:54,666
- Hold on.
- Good for you.

225
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,751
I'll call you later.

226
00:13:56,752 --> 00:13:57,794
Sorry.

227
00:13:57,795 --> 00:13:59,379
Wait, Bong Geun-dae.

228
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:01,881
- One of you, get in here.
- Hold on.

229
00:14:01,882 --> 00:14:03,716
- Hey, we should go.
- Yeah, after this.

230
00:14:03,717 --> 00:14:04,926
- A bit more.
- Group up.

231
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:06,011
Yeah, okay.

232
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,686
That was fast. Got the audio?

233
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:16,772
- Wait a minute.
- Why?

234
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:19,315
- I messed up.
- What?

235
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:20,358
Put these on.

236
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,777
- Here.
- Why should I?

237
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:24,362
- What are you doing?
- Hold on.

238
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:25,406
I failed. Stay still.

239
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:28,032
Put this in your right ear.

240
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:29,993
- Isn't this that thing?
- An earpiece.

241
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,619
- Isn't this eyeshadow?
- Yeah.

242
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,497
- What are you...
- Hold still.

243
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:36,667
It's done.

244
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:38,376
Just remember one thing.

245
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:41,338
A loser never makes eye contact.

246
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:42,923
A loser?

247
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:47,969
Fucking hell. What?

248
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:50,346
Let's just go, idiot. Something feels off.

249
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:53,976
- What the hell, dumbass?
- You're a fucking noob anyway. Let's go.

250
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:55,311
I said let's go.

251
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,026
Fuck, what are you doing?

252
00:15:03,235 --> 00:15:04,653
Are you freaking blind or what?

253
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:06,405
<i>Look down.</i>

254
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:10,992
You're fucking lucky.

255
00:15:10,993 --> 00:15:12,327
Don't let me see you again.

256
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:14,496
Quit acting dumb and fuck off, damn it.

257
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:19,792
It's because you flipped out.

258
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:22,170
<i>Inspector Im Han-rim,
good job holding back.</i>

259
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:24,465
Damn it, that fucking bastard.

260
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,887
Is it done? Testing.

261
00:15:31,847 --> 00:15:34,015
I'm done cloning Lee Chi-ho's voice.

262
00:15:34,016 --> 00:15:35,351
- Let's check it out.
- Okay.

263
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:38,770
- It's Chi-ho.
<i>- It's Chi-ho.</i>

264
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,980
- What's the password?
<i>- What's the password?</i>

265
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:42,231
Nice.

266
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:43,859
Wow.

267
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:49,113
- Okay, then. I'll call Jang Seong-gu now.
- I'm a bit nervous.

268
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:51,325
Don't be nervous. Just act natural.

269
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,079
<i>Hello?</i>

270
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:57,163
It's me, Chi-ho.

271
00:15:57,164 --> 00:16:00,209
I'd appreciate it
if you could give me the password.

272
00:16:00,876 --> 00:16:02,168
<i>Is this really Chi-ho?</i>

273
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:04,462
<i>You don't sound like yourself.</i>

274
00:16:04,463 --> 00:16:05,756
<i>- Who is this?</i>
- Let me.

275
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:12,345
You fucking asshole, who else would I be?
Goddamn idiot.

276
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,554
Give me the password.

277
00:16:13,555 --> 00:16:16,558
<i>It's Wi-Fi. "Wi-Fi" in Korean.</i>

278
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:28,528
The account belongs to Seong-gu,
but he doesn't have his own profile.

279
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:31,656
They've been sharing the same account.

280
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,950
I checked Seong-gu's food delivery app,

281
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:36,285
and he's had deliveries
to several addresses.

282
00:16:36,286 --> 00:16:38,454
There were even orders over 100,000 won.

283
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:40,832
He's subscribed to more than 20 games.

284
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,501
That's impossible
unless all he does is play games.

285
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:45,838
He had a lot of charges
for e-scooter rentals too.

286
00:16:46,505 --> 00:16:47,922
It says he's on one right now.

287
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:50,884
It says the food just got delivered.

288
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:53,845
He just logged into a game too.

289
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,597
Are you saying
Jang Seong-gu is on a scooter,

290
00:16:56,598 --> 00:17:00,060
eating with one hand
and playing a game with the other?

291
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:14,991
Do you really need to picture it?
It's obviously impossible.

292
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:16,951
Money isn't the real problem, is it?

293
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:19,204
What about the scam cases you looked into?

294
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:24,500
There's a website
where scam victims share information.

295
00:17:24,501 --> 00:17:26,044
I looked up Seong-gu's user ID,

296
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:29,505
and it showed reports of undelivered items
and fake sales on resale apps.

297
00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:31,007
They were all scam-related.

298
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:33,217
The punks used Seong-gu's ID
to post fake items,

299
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:35,762
then took the money
and ghosted the buyers.

300
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:39,141
Isn't this way too much
for just one kid to deal with on his own?

301
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:55,991
The goddamn scammer.

302
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,410
You scammed me over the AirPods,
didn't you?

303
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:02,080
No, it wasn't me. I really didn't do it.

304
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:03,956
Some kids stole my account.

305
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:06,293
- Really, I didn't--
- You son of a bitch.

306
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:08,377
It really wasn't me.

307
00:18:08,378 --> 00:18:12,965
You fucking asshole, you asked for it.
You bastard.

308
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:14,383
You goddamn bastard.

309
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:16,928
You little shit, trying to pull scams?
You wanna die?

310
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,807
You goddamn thief.
Give me my money back, you bastard.

311
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:22,601
Damn.

312
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,564
You idiot. Why'd you get caught?

313
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:36,323
He said I'll be sorry
if I don't pay him back.

314
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:37,824
And?

315
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:41,202
Chi-ho, I'm really sorry,
but I don't have any money.

316
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:43,747
- If you could help out a bit--
- That's too bad.

317
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,125
I've run out of allowance too.

318
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,710
You take care of it, okay?

319
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:50,170
Chi-ho.

320
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:52,505
Please, I'm asking you.

321
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,091
For God's sake.

322
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:58,177
I said I'd deal with it later.

323
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,763
Yeah, but when?

324
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,016
Should I break my promise?

325
00:19:05,227 --> 00:19:07,436
No, keep your promise.

326
00:19:07,437 --> 00:19:10,648
Do you know what would happen
if I changed my mind?

327
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:13,734
Everything is under your account
and your name, okay?

328
00:19:13,735 --> 00:19:15,319
You'll be the one who's fucked.

329
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,781
But I told you
I'd deal with everything later.

330
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,284
Super grateful, right?

331
00:19:23,620 --> 00:19:25,413
<i>My son tells me</i>

332
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:30,210
your son uses my son's account
to order food and spend money on games.

333
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:34,840
Take a look.
Hundreds of thousands of won were charged.

334
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:38,259
That's your side of the story.

335
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,388
I told Chi-ho to come home now,
so let's hear his side too.

336
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:45,767
There you are.

337
00:19:46,268 --> 00:19:47,311
Hey, Jang Seong-gu.

338
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:49,438
Go. It's okay.

339
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,191
You sent this crap to my sister?

340
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:57,862
You DMed her.

341
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,906
Oh my God, what is this?

342
00:19:59,907 --> 00:20:03,242
Seong-gu, did you really send her this?

343
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:05,036
Mom, I didn't do this.

344
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:07,747
- It's Chi-ho. He did this too.
- Excuse me?

345
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:10,541
Are you saying Chi-ho sent this
to his own sister?

346
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:12,001
Does that make any sense?

347
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:13,045
Are you crazy?

348
00:20:13,712 --> 00:20:16,380
- I should call the police. Unbelievable.
- Mom.

349
00:20:16,381 --> 00:20:17,674
No, wait.

350
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:19,300
I'm sorry.

351
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:22,553
If this offended you,
I apologize on his behalf.

352
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:24,138
Please forgive him this once.

353
00:20:24,139 --> 00:20:26,307
- Next time...
- This will never happen again.

354
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:29,352
...I'll send it to every girl in our class
using your account.

355
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:31,730
- Snitch on me again, dumbass.
- They're only kids.

356
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:36,776
- Ji-ho, you okay?
- Please forget why I came. I'm so...

357
00:20:36,777 --> 00:20:38,570
Hey, I'm so sorry. All right?

358
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,655
- Go.
- Are you insane?

359
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:42,073
Mom, it wasn't me.

360
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:43,449
Be quiet, you fool.

361
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:45,034
- Mom, it wasn't me.
- I'm sorry.

362
00:20:45,035 --> 00:20:47,496
Are you okay, Ji-ho?

363
00:20:50,832 --> 00:20:51,667
Yeah.

364
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:53,460
Thanks.

365
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:56,296
All right.

366
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:02,677
Chi-ho, do you mind if I take a call?

367
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:04,720
Can't you see I'm playing a game?

368
00:21:04,721 --> 00:21:06,722
It's going to lag.

369
00:21:06,723 --> 00:21:07,641
It's my mom.

370
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:09,977
Damn it.

371
00:21:10,477 --> 00:21:11,311
Answer, idiot.

372
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:16,107
Hello?

373
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:18,777
<i>What the hell have you been up to?</i>

374
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:21,862
How much is all this?

375
00:21:21,863 --> 00:21:22,780
FOODMON ORDER HISTORY

376
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:26,158
When I paid this off for you before,
I said that was the last time.

377
00:21:26,159 --> 00:21:28,494
How many times is this now?

378
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:31,456
How am I supposed to make sense of this?

379
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:37,587
Jang Seong-gu. Don't you have
anything to say to me? Well?

380
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:39,880
Don't tell me it was your friend again.

381
00:21:39,881 --> 00:21:41,674
It really wasn't me.

382
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:44,594
After all that humiliation last time,
you're lying again?

383
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:49,558
Why are you growing up like this?
What's suddenly gotten into you?

384
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:52,728
Seriously...

385
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:35,812
Seong-gu wants to tell you everything
Lee Chi-ho has done to him.

386
00:22:37,064 --> 00:22:38,357
You'll tell him, right?

387
00:22:40,734 --> 00:22:41,568
Yes.

388
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,945
I'll tell you everything.

389
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:47,574
He says I can trust the ERPB.

390
00:22:55,582 --> 00:22:57,918
<i>Do you think
the ERPB won't believe you either?</i>

391
00:23:04,966 --> 00:23:07,386
If the ERPB had existed two years ago

392
00:23:08,345 --> 00:23:10,097
and had come

393
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:12,974
to our school...

394
00:23:18,105 --> 00:23:20,690
I wouldn't have killed anyone...

395
00:23:22,859 --> 00:23:24,945
and no one would've died.

396
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,073
Inspector Na Hwa-jin will be different.

397
00:23:29,741 --> 00:23:31,868
He's just like Ms. Choi.

398
00:23:38,041 --> 00:23:40,502
HE USED MY IDENTITY ON VARIOUS WEBSITES
TO SCAM PEOPLE

399
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:43,046
Yes.

400
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:46,091
Inspector.

401
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:51,763
Well, did you hear about
the School Violence Committee meeting?

402
00:23:54,015 --> 00:23:58,979
Chi-ho reported Seong-gu for bullying.

403
00:24:00,147 --> 00:24:00,981
What?

404
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:10,574
SCHOOL VIOLENCE DELIBERATION COMMITTEE

405
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:15,703
VICTIM STUDENT

406
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:18,915
ACCUSED STUDENT

407
00:24:23,086 --> 00:24:24,546
Just a moment.

408
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:28,299
An ERPB inspector cannot legally serve
on the committee.

409
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:29,383
Please have him leave.

410
00:24:29,384 --> 00:24:33,138
We also received a report
and have been monitoring the situation,

411
00:24:33,805 --> 00:24:36,223
so we need to understand what happened.

412
00:24:36,224 --> 00:24:38,100
I'll simply observe.

413
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:39,436
Speaking is not permitted.

414
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:40,896
Yes, sir.

415
00:24:41,897 --> 00:24:46,233
All right. We will now begin
the review of the school violence case

416
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,651
at Jinwon High School.

417
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:51,113
First, we will hear the statement
from the victim's side.

418
00:24:51,114 --> 00:24:53,616
Even before the incident
was fully investigated,

419
00:24:53,617 --> 00:24:56,869
Jang Seong-gu spread false rumors
about Lee Chi-ho

420
00:24:56,870 --> 00:25:00,873
and called in the ERPB,
effectively branding him as the bully.

421
00:25:00,874 --> 00:25:03,125
He is in severe psychological distress.

422
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:06,796
His psychiatric treatment records
are hereby submitted as evidence.

423
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:13,887
DEPRESSIVE DISORDER
PANIC DISORDER

424
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:17,682
Next, we will hear from the accused.
Please make your statement.

425
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,522
Oh, I...

426
00:25:31,238 --> 00:25:32,405
This isn't fair.

427
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:37,786
I'm the victim here.

428
00:25:40,247 --> 00:25:43,083
They stole my accounts.

429
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:46,544
They used them to run scams,

430
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:47,712
play games,

431
00:25:48,588 --> 00:25:49,838
and order food.

432
00:25:49,839 --> 00:25:51,299
Is there any evidence?

433
00:25:53,176 --> 00:25:55,470
Do you have any evidence
that they stole your accounts?

434
00:25:56,471 --> 00:25:57,721
Well, that's--

435
00:25:57,722 --> 00:26:00,392
As you can see, his claim is one-sided
with no evidence.

436
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:03,852
We cannot rule out
that he might be making false statements.

437
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:06,523
If so, it could constitute defamation.

438
00:26:19,869 --> 00:26:22,371
You'll see if you look at the records.

439
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:25,165
I'm online at an Internet café
while on an e-scooter

440
00:26:25,166 --> 00:26:27,835
and having food delivered elsewhere.
If you see the logs--

441
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:29,044
That's right.

442
00:26:29,045 --> 00:26:32,506
Lee Chi-ho said he borrowed his accounts
a few times for urgent reasons.

443
00:26:32,507 --> 00:26:33,757
It wasn't a few times--

444
00:26:33,758 --> 00:26:35,218
Only answer

445
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:38,096
what you're asked.

446
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:44,435
Once or twice, Chi-ho borrowed
his streaming service account

447
00:26:44,436 --> 00:26:46,895
and used his account
to rent a bike a few times.

448
00:26:46,896 --> 00:26:48,188
That's all.

449
00:26:48,189 --> 00:26:53,277
And yet, Chi-ho wanted to help his friend
and sent Jang Seong-gu money.

450
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:55,112
I never received any money.

451
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:56,990
Please check your bank account.

452
00:27:04,164 --> 00:27:05,372
SEJIN TRANSACTION ACCOUNT

453
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:07,709
LEE CHI-HO / REPAYMENT
DEPOSIT 1,000,000 WON

454
00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:17,384
By contrast,

455
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:20,471
the harm Lee Chi-ho has suffered
is very serious.

456
00:27:20,472 --> 00:27:22,848
Deemed a bully, based on unfounded claims,

457
00:27:22,849 --> 00:27:24,892
he is being shunned
and isolated at school.

458
00:27:24,893 --> 00:27:27,645
But what's more concerning
is that this false narrative

459
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:30,022
is even threatening Chi-ho's future.

460
00:27:30,023 --> 00:27:32,399
This is not simply defamation.

461
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:34,235
It is social character assassination.

462
00:27:35,195 --> 00:27:38,322
Of course, we do not intend
to pursue criminal charges.

463
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:41,076
However, we have submitted
the psychiatric records,

464
00:27:41,576 --> 00:27:43,786
and given his struggles
to keep up with studies,

465
00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:48,540
we believe an appropriate mediation,
compensation, or settlement is needed.

466
00:27:48,541 --> 00:27:50,085
A settlement?

467
00:27:51,670 --> 00:27:52,629
How much...

468
00:27:53,463 --> 00:27:57,341
That said,
since it's a matter between children,

469
00:27:57,342 --> 00:27:59,426
Chi-ho's mother, a truly admirable woman,

470
00:27:59,427 --> 00:28:03,098
wishes to receive an apology
and settle the matter here.

471
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:06,267
What do you say, Seong-gu's mother?

472
00:28:14,818 --> 00:28:16,403
Chi-ho's mother.

473
00:28:17,987 --> 00:28:19,239
Thank you so much.

474
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:22,741
I'll make sure this never happens again.

475
00:28:22,742 --> 00:28:25,912
I really appreciate your leniency.

476
00:28:26,413 --> 00:28:27,622
Chi-ho.

477
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:29,749
I'm sorry, all right?

478
00:28:30,417 --> 00:28:32,043
I'm really sorry.

479
00:28:32,544 --> 00:28:33,586
My goodness, ma'am...

480
00:28:35,171 --> 00:28:36,423
<i>So that's the situation.</i>

481
00:28:37,465 --> 00:28:38,758
Understood, sir.

482
00:28:42,929 --> 00:28:44,264
Can you believe this?

483
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:46,849
He did wrong,
yet he calls for the meeting.

484
00:28:46,850 --> 00:28:49,310
He even hired an expensive lawyer!

485
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:55,150
These days, I hear lawyers specializing
in school bullying provide manuals.

486
00:28:56,025 --> 00:28:59,570
"File a complaint first.
That way, you can claim victim status."

487
00:28:59,571 --> 00:29:02,823
"File a counter-report.
That's how it turns into mutual fault."

488
00:29:02,824 --> 00:29:04,116
They say things like this.

489
00:29:04,117 --> 00:29:06,786
But still,
what's the School Violence Committee for?

490
00:29:07,287 --> 00:29:10,164
It should be able to determine the truth!

491
00:29:10,165 --> 00:29:13,167
But it's not that easy in reality.

492
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:17,129
They have to review the case,
meet the students briefly,

493
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:19,256
and reach a decision all on the same day.

494
00:29:19,257 --> 00:29:21,800
Since that's difficult,
they just look at the evidence,

495
00:29:21,801 --> 00:29:24,846
but they struggle
to decide who is at fault,

496
00:29:25,346 --> 00:29:28,599
handing down
similar rulings over and over.

497
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:30,226
What should we do?

498
00:29:30,727 --> 00:29:32,479
Damn it, what are we going to do?

499
00:29:54,417 --> 00:29:56,336
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE

500
00:30:06,387 --> 00:30:08,014
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE, WEAK CONNECTION

501
00:30:17,273 --> 00:30:21,945
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE, STRONG CONNECTION

502
00:30:53,059 --> 00:30:54,310
There you are.

503
00:31:24,716 --> 00:31:26,885
It's okay to cry out loud, Seong-gu.

504
00:31:27,886 --> 00:31:29,387
Why are you holding it in?

505
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:36,936
If you hold it in,

506
00:31:38,229 --> 00:31:39,814
no one will know you're crying.

507
00:31:42,275 --> 00:31:43,943
If you don't speak up,

508
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:46,779
no one will know you've been wronged.

509
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:52,660
And if you're curled up like this,
they'll never know what they did wrong.

510
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:00,793
Is this how you want to live?

511
00:32:16,684 --> 00:32:18,686
All right, then.

512
00:32:30,740 --> 00:32:32,200
It's not fair!

513
00:32:32,784 --> 00:32:35,078
It's so unfair. It's driving me crazy.

514
00:32:42,418 --> 00:32:44,127
I told the police.

515
00:32:44,128 --> 00:32:47,256
I told my parents and my teachers.

