Like my son says, if it's an act...

775
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:37,317
Stop it! Oh my goodness.

776
00:45:39,236 --> 00:45:40,654
How does it feel?

777
00:45:42,322 --> 00:45:44,283
Are you finally asking yourself,

778
00:45:44,867 --> 00:45:45,993
"Why did I do that?"

779
00:45:49,413 --> 00:45:51,622
Will it only sink in
if your finger gets broken?

780
00:45:51,623 --> 00:45:53,207
Oh my God, what's wrong with her?

781
00:45:53,208 --> 00:45:55,085
All right, Inspector Im Han-rim.

782
00:45:56,545 --> 00:45:57,504
Oh no, my son.

783
00:45:59,423 --> 00:46:01,884
Inspector Im Han-rim here

784
00:46:02,384 --> 00:46:05,720
is actually an ERPB field investigator
who was assigned

785
00:46:05,721 --> 00:46:08,307
to look into the bullying case
involving Jang Seong-gu.

786
00:46:08,932 --> 00:46:11,226
Right, so that's what's been going on.

787
00:46:12,394 --> 00:46:14,938
So why did we go to such lengths?

788
00:46:15,439 --> 00:46:18,734
It's because of Jang Seong-gu.

789
00:46:22,946 --> 00:46:24,281
Seong-gu!

790
00:46:25,866 --> 00:46:26,867
You see us, right?

791
00:46:39,213 --> 00:46:40,088
Yes.

792
00:46:40,714 --> 00:46:44,426
We are here to clear his name.

793
00:46:46,386 --> 00:46:47,596
How does it feel?

794
00:46:48,889 --> 00:46:51,850
Do you finally realize

795
00:46:52,392 --> 00:46:53,643
what you did to Seong-gu?

796
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:56,104
This is really not fair.

797
00:46:57,564 --> 00:46:59,482
I never even laid a finger on Seong-gu.

798
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:01,860
That's right. You never hit him.

799
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:05,531
There's not a scratch on him.
But do you think it wasn't violence?

800
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:09,368
You never touched him,

801
00:47:10,577 --> 00:47:12,787
yet he was scared, terrified,

802
00:47:12,788 --> 00:47:15,082
wronged, and frustrated.

803
00:47:15,582 --> 00:47:18,210
No one believed him,
no matter what he said.

804
00:47:18,710 --> 00:47:20,879
Not even his parents. That's right.

805
00:47:21,630 --> 00:47:24,048
He probably thought
it'd be better to be beaten.

806
00:47:24,049 --> 00:47:24,967
Why?

807
00:47:25,467 --> 00:47:27,427
Because if he had marks from it,

808
00:47:29,179 --> 00:47:31,098
his parents might believe him.

809
00:47:32,474 --> 00:47:34,142
<i>Do you know what's worse?</i>

810
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:37,019
<i>To get out of the situation,</i>

811
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:40,857
<i>he had no choice but to beg
the very person who put him there.</i>

812
00:47:40,858 --> 00:47:43,777
The victim had no choice
but to bow his head...

813
00:47:46,613 --> 00:47:48,866
and plead with the bully.

814
00:47:50,409 --> 00:47:52,202
This is what you did to Seong-gu.

815
00:47:52,995 --> 00:47:54,580
Without laying a finger on him.

816
00:48:02,921 --> 00:48:04,464
It's been hard for you, hasn't it?

817
00:48:05,048 --> 00:48:08,010
It must've been so hard, all on your own.

818
00:48:08,510 --> 00:48:10,804
Seong-gu, I'm sorry. All right?

819
00:48:11,305 --> 00:48:15,016
I was such a fool.

820
00:48:15,017 --> 00:48:17,811
I should've believed you.

821
00:48:21,481 --> 00:48:23,233
Our investigation found

822
00:48:23,817 --> 00:48:27,738
that Lee Chi-ho's testimony
about suffering harm

823
00:48:28,322 --> 00:48:30,823
because of Jang Seong-gu was false

824
00:48:30,824 --> 00:48:33,576
and that the actual victim
is Jang Seong-gu.

825
00:48:33,577 --> 00:48:35,703
Accordingly, the ERPB will implement

826
00:48:35,704 --> 00:48:39,290
appropriate protective measures
for the victim, Jang Seong-gu, at once.

827
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:43,295
Additionally, the prior ruling against him
by the School Violence Committee

828
00:48:44,087 --> 00:48:48,008
will be fully nullified
by the authority of the ERPB.

829
00:48:51,011 --> 00:48:52,846
A victim is a victim.

830
00:48:53,555 --> 00:48:54,973
A bully is a bully.

831
00:48:57,351 --> 00:48:59,353
Is that so difficult?

832
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:08,278
Adults should protect children.

833
00:49:10,072 --> 00:49:12,074
Aren't you ashamed to face them?

834
00:49:33,887 --> 00:49:36,097
Thank you for helping me.

835
00:49:36,098 --> 00:49:38,100
You'll be issued a new resident number.

836
00:49:38,684 --> 00:49:39,892
Do well at school.

837
00:49:39,893 --> 00:49:41,602
Thank you, sir.

838
00:49:41,603 --> 00:49:43,437
Thank you so much.

839
00:49:43,438 --> 00:49:44,689
It's finally over, ma'am.

840
00:49:44,690 --> 00:49:47,901
I'll make sure to raise Seong-gu well.

841
00:49:48,902 --> 00:49:50,319
Go home with your mother.

842
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,238
Okay.

843
00:49:58,328 --> 00:49:59,162
Your friend?

844
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:00,914
Well.

845
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:15,137
I'm sorry.

846
00:50:15,721 --> 00:50:17,431
You told me not to do anything.

847
00:50:19,516 --> 00:50:20,474
But still,

848
00:50:20,475 --> 00:50:23,895
something good happened
because I did what I could.

849
00:50:25,063 --> 00:50:26,273
I'm glad.

850
00:50:48,295 --> 00:50:49,755
Welcome.

851
00:51:04,186 --> 00:51:05,896
Get your own glass.

852
00:51:06,396 --> 00:51:08,648
That's for Ga-yun.

853
00:51:39,888 --> 00:51:41,056
Lie down here.

854
00:51:42,265 --> 00:51:43,308
Careful.

855
00:52:03,662 --> 00:52:04,788
Hey.

856
00:52:06,790 --> 00:52:08,458
You should find another woman.

857
00:52:09,417 --> 00:52:10,252
Goodness.

858
00:52:11,962 --> 00:52:14,464
Ga-yun would be mad at me, you know?

859
00:52:15,507 --> 00:52:17,259
Imagine if she heard that.

860
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:22,097
She'd go on at you
for a couple of hours at least.

861
00:52:22,722 --> 00:52:23,807
You know.

862
00:52:29,855 --> 00:52:30,772
God.

863
00:52:47,664 --> 00:52:49,249
<i>Busted.</i>

864
00:52:52,169 --> 00:52:53,086
No way.

865
00:52:57,507 --> 00:52:59,050
Fine, I won't smoke.

866
00:53:28,622 --> 00:53:29,623
<i>Here.</i>

867
00:53:30,373 --> 00:53:31,208
<i>Cheers!</i>

868
00:53:32,125 --> 00:53:34,711
Why would I toast with this guy?

869
00:53:35,795 --> 00:53:38,465
I don't toast with someone
who doesn't like me either.

870
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:45,471
Are you really going to be like this?

871
00:53:45,472 --> 00:53:46,597
Yeah, I am.

872
00:53:46,598 --> 00:53:47,974
He leaves me no choice.

873
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:51,353
Fine, then.

874
00:53:52,812 --> 00:53:53,772
I won't get married.

875
00:53:55,232 --> 00:53:56,900
Where'd that come from?

876
00:53:57,567 --> 00:53:58,400
Good.

877
00:53:58,401 --> 00:54:00,946
Yeah. But I'll never get married.

878
00:54:02,197 --> 00:54:04,074
- Never?
- Yeah.

879
00:54:04,658 --> 00:54:06,283
If I can't marry Hwa-jin,

880
00:54:06,284 --> 00:54:08,328
I'll just live alone
till I get old and die.

881
00:54:08,912 --> 00:54:12,122
Then, Dad, you'll never get to hold
your grandchild

882
00:54:12,123 --> 00:54:15,752
or hear them call you "Grandpa."
You'll just grow old.

883
00:54:16,253 --> 00:54:20,465
If you don't want that,
should you be acting like this or not?

884
00:54:21,049 --> 00:54:22,801
Well, that can't happen.

885
00:54:24,636 --> 00:54:28,181
Then do you think
you two should be toasting or not?

886
00:54:30,433 --> 00:54:31,268
Shall we?

887
00:54:32,227 --> 00:54:33,686
Make it a couples' shot.

888
00:54:33,687 --> 00:54:35,479
That's gross. Why would we do that?

889
00:54:35,480 --> 00:54:38,023
Then I won't get married.
Whatever. I'm recording.

890
00:54:38,024 --> 00:54:39,149
- Ga-yun, that's...
- Wait.

891
00:54:39,150 --> 00:54:40,359
- One...
- Hold on. Hey.

892
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:41,277
Two...

893
00:54:41,278 --> 00:54:42,654
Three!

894
00:56:12,327 --> 00:56:13,953
For fuck's sake.

895
00:56:14,537 --> 00:56:15,372
Hey.

896
00:56:16,122 --> 00:56:16,956
Damn it.

897
00:56:18,583 --> 00:56:20,376
You said I'd win.

898
00:56:20,377 --> 00:56:22,545
You said if I got a lawyer,
it'd be game over.

899
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:28,968
File a report first.

900
00:56:29,469 --> 00:56:30,720
Why should I?

901
00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:32,054
What for?

902
00:56:32,055 --> 00:56:35,225
I don't think you can afford
to be this relaxed right now.

903
00:56:35,934 --> 00:56:40,772
The ERPB will do everything they can
to brand you as the bully.

904
00:56:41,272 --> 00:56:42,940
Then you'll at least get suspended.

905
00:56:42,941 --> 00:56:43,942
No,

906
00:56:44,818 --> 00:56:46,027
you may even get expelled.

907
00:56:50,281 --> 00:56:52,200
You need to lay the groundwork first.

908
00:56:53,118 --> 00:56:55,703
The first one to file
becomes the victim in today's world.

909
00:56:56,871 --> 00:57:00,333
If you don't want to be branded
as the bully, act like the victim.

910
00:57:01,584 --> 00:57:03,002
This person will help you.

911
00:57:03,503 --> 00:57:04,921
ATTORNEY YOON TAE-GYEONG

912
00:57:06,005 --> 00:57:07,424
<i>Now what?</i>

913
00:57:08,716 --> 00:57:12,095
- I think everything went as planned.
- Fucking hell.

914
00:57:12,595 --> 00:57:15,265
What the fuck are you talking about?

915
00:57:17,183 --> 00:57:19,769
Hey, my life's over because of the ERPB.

916
00:57:20,937 --> 00:57:22,980
It's over for my family because of me.

917
00:57:22,981 --> 00:57:25,733
I feel like I have to fucking die
to end this.

918
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:29,946
So how can you say it went as planned?
You bastard.

919
00:57:31,281 --> 00:57:33,783
I reported you to the ERPB
for bullying Jang Seong-gu

920
00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:36,161
so they would come after you.

921
00:57:37,745 --> 00:57:39,247
Do you know what happens next?

922
00:57:40,582 --> 00:57:41,416
This.

923
00:57:52,927 --> 00:57:55,679
MIRAE DAEHAN PARTY

924
00:57:55,680 --> 00:57:57,182
Sir.

925
00:58:00,059 --> 00:58:01,227
Have you seen this?

926
00:58:01,728 --> 00:58:03,604
The ERPB is in serious trouble.

927
00:58:03,605 --> 00:58:06,816
Something happened
while they were at Jinwon High.

928
00:58:11,362 --> 00:58:13,197
Sir, you have a visitor.

929
00:58:13,198 --> 00:58:14,115
Let them in.

930
00:58:15,200 --> 00:58:16,034
Well.

931
00:58:17,452 --> 00:58:19,746
What brings you here at this hour?

932
00:58:21,915 --> 00:58:22,748
Have a seat.

933
00:58:22,749 --> 00:58:23,665
Okay.

934
00:58:23,666 --> 00:58:26,085
Please bring us some tea.

935
00:58:27,086 --> 00:58:27,921
Sure.

936
00:58:28,963 --> 00:58:33,550
Wait, shouldn't you be on your way
to school right now?

937
00:58:33,551 --> 00:58:35,511
I have something to give you.

938
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:37,596
I'll be on my way after I give you this.

939
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:40,016
I can't miss school.

940
00:58:43,186 --> 00:58:45,104
<i>My life's over because of the ERPB.</i>

941
00:58:45,730 --> 00:58:47,439
<i>It's over for my family because of me.</i>

942
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:50,360
<i>I feel like I have to fucking die
to end this.</i>

943
00:58:52,695 --> 00:58:54,864
What is this?

944
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:56,950
It's what you wanted.

945
00:58:59,953 --> 00:59:01,286
Oh, it's okay.

946
00:59:01,287 --> 00:59:02,997
There were no cameras.

947
00:59:07,335 --> 00:59:08,962
It's not that I don't trust you.

948
00:59:10,296 --> 00:59:12,924
You can decide how you want to use it.

949
00:59:21,891 --> 00:59:24,561
STUDENT FALLS FROM JINWON HIGH ROOFTOP
SUICIDE SUSPECTED

950
00:59:25,979 --> 00:59:26,813
Hey.

951
00:59:28,481 --> 00:59:30,775
What the hell did you do?

952
00:59:31,442 --> 00:59:33,528
You think I got you out
so you could do this?

953
00:59:34,988 --> 00:59:35,989
Oh.

954
00:59:37,115 --> 00:59:38,199
That's not it.

955
00:59:40,785 --> 00:59:42,912
You didn't get me out.

956
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:46,124
I planned all of this.

957
00:59:49,877 --> 00:59:50,711
What?

958
00:59:50,712 --> 00:59:52,963
You didn't drag me into this.

959
00:59:52,964 --> 00:59:55,258
I dragged you into it.

960
00:59:55,967 --> 00:59:58,678
I sent Officer Kang to you.

961
01:00:17,155 --> 01:00:18,239
PAROLE REVIEW MATERIALS

962
01:00:20,033 --> 01:00:22,535
DEEMED SUITABLE FOR SOCIAL REINTEGRATION
THROUGH PAROLE

963
01:00:26,539 --> 01:00:31,169
It really helped that you pulled strings
with the parole board.

964
01:00:31,669 --> 01:00:32,503
Thank you.

965
01:00:34,047 --> 01:00:35,048
You little shit!

966
01:00:37,717 --> 01:00:38,801
Now, don't swear.

967
01:00:39,719 --> 01:00:42,597
If you want to be president,
you should keep your dignity.

968
01:00:44,807 --> 01:00:47,060
At the end of the day,
you and I are the same.

969
01:00:47,727 --> 01:00:50,104
We both want to bring down the ERPB.

970
01:01:23,596 --> 01:01:26,515
Minister, how is Lee Chi-ho doing
right now?

971
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:28,642
- Have you seen him?
- It's Hwang Gi-tae.

972
01:01:28,643 --> 01:01:30,227
Are you here to see Lee Chi-ho?

973
01:01:30,228 --> 01:01:34,022
How do you respond to another incident
like this happening at Jinwon High?

974
01:01:34,023 --> 01:01:35,441
What's going on?

975
01:01:36,150 --> 01:01:38,527
Mr. Hwang, what brings you here?

976
01:01:38,528 --> 01:01:41,029
The entire country is in uproar
over this tragedy.

977
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:42,198
How could I not come?

978
01:01:44,325 --> 01:01:46,119
For now, his treatment is the priority.

979
01:01:46,619 --> 01:01:47,452
You should leave.

980
01:01:47,453 --> 01:01:50,832
I don't think you're in a position
to be saying that.

981
01:01:58,881 --> 01:02:00,633
<i>My life's over because of the ERPB.</i>

982
01:02:01,426 --> 01:02:03,427
<i>It's over for my family because of me.</i>

983
01:02:03,428 --> 01:02:06,305
<i>I feel like I have to fucking die
to end this.</i>

984
01:02:09,016 --> 01:02:10,977
Do you honestly believe

985
01:02:11,477 --> 01:02:14,188
the ERPB played no part
in what happened to Lee Chi-ho?

986
01:02:17,608 --> 01:02:20,986
<i>The release of an audio clip
of a Jinwon High School student</i>

987
01:02:20,987 --> 01:02:23,780
<i>who allegedly attempted suicide
has shocked the public.</i>

988
01:02:23,781 --> 01:02:28,201
<i>The five-second clip
that is going viral on social media</i>

989
01:02:28,202 --> 01:02:32,664
<i>features the student's own voice
expressing resentment toward the ERPB.</i>

990
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:34,958
<i>The police are focusing
their investigation</i>

991
01:02:34,959 --> 01:02:38,044
<i>on the clip's authenticity,
who recorded it,</i>

992
01:02:38,045 --> 01:02:39,630
<i>and how it was distributed.</i>

993
01:02:40,131 --> 01:02:42,549
<i>The political sphere
is also taking immediate action,</i>

994
01:02:42,550 --> 01:02:45,427
<i>calling for an urgent inquiry to determine</i>

995
01:02:45,428 --> 01:02:47,637
<i>whether there were
any unlawful acts or coercion</i>

996
01:02:47,638 --> 01:02:49,681
<i>during the ERPB's investigation.</i>

997
01:02:49,682 --> 01:02:50,933
JINWON HIGH SCHOOL

998
01:04:52,305 --> 01:04:55,266
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim
